caption: Definitely love the ambiance and the hospitality. Their Jerk pasta Alfredo is the truth. If you’re in the Flatbush area of Brooklyn be sure to check this place out. You will not regret it. I promise you that!!

Overall I enjoyed my experience at the MangoSeed during a Sunday brunch. The food was well seasoned, portions are satisfying, and the staff was accommodating. There is a humble but inviting outdoor dining area in the back of the restaurant. My only con is that the music was so loud I had to use my earplugs just to save myself from the ringing in my ears. I’m a musician so admittedly I’m particularly sensitive to blowing out my eardrums with loud sounds. However, I felt like I was in a club.  While I enjoyed dancing in my seat, the music selections were great but much too loud to allow for any descent conversation with my friends. Go ready to enjoy a club like atmosphere, solid food options with a side of interesting cocktails, of which I may try upon my next visit.

A friend and I had drinks at Mango Seed and dinner at Zurlee’s (sister restaurant/bar) last night in celebration of my friends birthday. She a lawyer and I a tenured NYC educator. Upon receiving our bill, I provided the bar tender my debit card (I was issued a temporary card yesterday as I lost my primary bank card on vacation and was awaiting my new card to arrive in the mail). The bar tender refused to use my temporary card because it did not have my name on it and inferred I could potentially be a suspect of scamming. Puzzled, My friend and I explained to the bartender calmly my temporary card was linked to my bank account and I had ID to prove the card was my own and not a gift card or scam. The bartender continued to refuse and dismiss my payment option. I immediately demanded to speak to the manager who provided me an inaccurate excuse about the restaurants policy and due to the “high volume of crime fraud and scamming from the neighborhood in the past” this absurd policy was in place. I was forced to use an ATM in a laundry mat where my card could have been potentially compromised to the pay. As a native of brooklyn and more specifically the Flatbush neighborhood I am completely appalled at the actions that took place at MangoSeed. It was embarrassing and speaks to the character and integrity of the restaurant. I have been a patron of MangoSeed for years and never had any issues until last night. It was extremely uncalled for and has left a last impression and bad taste in my mouth. With that said, I will be sharing this post on all of my social media’s and passing this to members of my professional organizations. I was discriminated in my own neighborhood which before my eyes is changing. I suspect if I were another race I would not have been treated the way I was treated. So thank you MangoSeed for showing your true colors. I will never again frequent any of your establishments

If you are looking for a place that serves good drinks and great Caribbean food this is your spot. I usually come on Tuesday nights because they have awesome drink specials. I'm huge on appetizers so they have this bomb-ass Jerk fish tacos and their macaroni and cheese is so creamy and good not like the fake stuff. Oh and how can I forget the drinks!!! They're sweet and strong - just how I like it. How can you go wrong!! My two faves are the guava mojito and and strawberry margarita. Now onto the dinner I have only tasted the  Mango Pico de gallo Salmon and the " Rasta Pasta" (it isn't as good as the one at Foot Prints)-but it isn't bad either. So if you ever in town and looking for a chill spot with good vibes and great food give this place a try!! I promise you it won't disappoint.

Okay, so I've officially been brought over to the MangoSeed side. I'm not going to lie, I've been resistant to them since they've open for quite some time. I have a "thing" about going out to eat at establishments whose cuisine I can cook. So if anything else, COME FOR THE HAPPY HOUR!! Mon-Fri 4-7 then 10-until close. My drink to date is the Sugar Cane Lemonade. It is HELLA" refreshing and it gets the job done simultaneously! So I've never gotten around the main dishes because I'm absolutely in love with the jerk fish tacos and the mac and cheese. The jerk fish tacos is actually made with salmon and the shell is dipped in beet juice to give it that bright red color so technically clean eating. (I know what I said, don't judge.) The mac n' cheese is an easy HIT. It's not your average mac n cheese with one of the cheeses is smoked Gouda. I'm literally thinking about the next time I can go without feeling bad as I type.......

Pretty good restaurant. It's family owned and cozy (or crowded depending on how you view it). Food is okay and service was decent. The happy hour drinks blew my mind! $5 and $6 for such delicious drinks! Awesome! We sat in the back ... view wasn't the best because they didn't decorate or make it look nice, it just felt like someone's backyard with a deck and some grass in the back.  We wanted to go outside because the music inside seemed to overpower any conversation anyone would anticipate. I kinda felt like we should've been inside though, as we really felt left out from the crowd and the feel of the restaurant.  Overall, good food and somewhat decent service, clean bathrooms and great drinks... it's a great place to grab a bite with some friends in the Flatbush area.  Recommendations-  if you're okay with loud music, please sit inside or you'll feel like you're just eating in someone's backyard therefore totally missing the vibe of the restaurant. Another thing is to make reservations ahead of time as there appears to be a wait time. My group had a reservation but while waited to be seated we overheard others at the bar talking about a 45 minute wait.

Went to mangoseed before a show at Kings Theatre with my wife. When we arrived, because we didn't have reservations the hostess said we would have to wait for about 20-25 minutes. She returned around 15 minutes later and sat us. The drinks were about 4 out of five. Food was great. Hospitality was great. My total experience was 4.5 out of 5. My only issue was as we waited at the bar, the bartender never made it to us to offer us a beverage. It wasn't his fault. It was busy and he was the only bartender but still worthy of taking away 0.5!!!! One additional bartender on a Friday, on a Kings Theatre night would have made the event exceptional.

My favorite place to go, if you're seeking a caribbean cuisine, a really good meal or a place to spend time with friends/family over drinks this is the absolute best option in the area hands down. Food is AMAZING and once you go you'll for sure return!
